Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In 2016, Mongolia reported one outbreak of FMD in the province of Govisumber associated with serotype A. The event was resolved in August 2016. See event summaries and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=20542.

In 2015, Mongolia reported 6 outbreaks of FMD associated with serotype O. See event summaries and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=17308 and http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=18884, respectively.

Information published by the Pirbright World Reference Laboratory for Foot-and-Mouth Disease, shows that the following serotypes have been identified in Mongolia:
1. FMDV-untyped: 1931 to 1973 (types O and A occurred intermittently between 1931 to 1973 (Nyamsuren et al, 2006).
2. FMDV-O: 1974, 2000 - 2002, 2004, 2010, 2014-2015
3. FMDV-A: 2013-2013, 2016
4. FMDV-Asia 1: 2005

See data at http://www.wrlfmd.org/fmd_genotyping/asia/mog.htm. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4836897,1.]
